attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is an IoT botnet agent, likely a variant of Mirai or Gafgyt, designed for distributed denial-of-service (DDoS) attacks and automated exploitation. Key malicious behaviors include: 1) Exploitation: It contains strings and logic (sub_4051bd) for the Huawei HG532 TR-064 remote code execution vulnerability (CVE-2017-17215), using SOAP payloads to inject shell commands via 'DeviceUpgrade_1'. 2) Process Killing: It enumerates /proc/ to find and terminate competing malware processes (sub_400755, sub_400957). 3) C2 Communication: It establishes network connections to 158.94.210.71 and attempts to download additional payloads from bigbins.rebirth[.]st using wget. 4) Fingerprinting: It gathers system information from /proc/cpuinfo and /proc/self/exe to tailor its execution environment.
